\label{Tab:3.1}
\end{table}

Figure \ref{Fig:3.2}(a) demonstrates the $\beta$ dependent $\mu(E)$ for a SiC device; whereas, Fig. \ref{Fig:3.2}(b) illustrates dependence of $\upsilon(E)$ on the chosen values of $\beta$ as given in \eqref{Eq:3.2}. The simulated values of both $\upsilon(E)$ and $\mu(E)$ are identical to those which are reported in the literature for SiC devices \cite{Mnatsakanov2002,Lv2004,Bertilsson2001,Roschke2001}.

Figure \ref{Fig:3.2} was plotted by using the data given in Table \ref{Tab:3.1}. Plots of Fig. \ref{Fig:3.2} show that by considering the material quality, device geometry and biasing conditions, $\alpha$, $\beta$ and $N_r$ can be chosen appropriately to achieve a reasonable match between modeled and experimental characteristics of SiC MESFETs.

